pr_review_comment_body:
@adriangb check field.py and functional_validators.py for examples of examples in docstrings.

You don't have to use the "Example:" heading. That just puts the example in a pop-out admonition when built in the docs. You can also include the example code inline with the description part of the docstring.

Note that examples are tested even in docstrings.

See https://github.com/dotnet/core/pull/6170#discussion_r615006176.  The test code I've used to exercise the X11 path is the following:

```csharp
var g = Graphics.FromImage(new Bitmap(10, 10));
g.CopyFromScreen(new Point(0, 0), new Point(1, 1), new Size(1, 1));
```

