@percyliang Based on our discussion yesterday, I altered the database query logic to use join query on all dependencies. Changes are listed at https://github.com/codalab/codalab-worksheets/pull/2148. 
For the use case when there is no dependency provided, if we do want to include functionality to handle this, I don't think the logic can be combined with the one with dependencies. On the other hand, if we really don't want to handle this case, then I'll remove this piece of logic. 
I personally think providing the ability to return a memoized bundle without dependencies would be helpful especially in the case when the bundle might take a long time to finish. Suppose one user submitted a bundle that took a few hours to finish, after 1 month or so, he/she wanted to run it again, then they could really take advantage of using the memozie option. Let me know how you think!

I was puzzled by this line before – now you moved it from one function to the other (because you moved that function from one class to the other).

@kba Please explain the reason for this in the first place!

Frankly, I don't know what unittest or pytest is supposed to do with our import-time state change. We have no explicit module or class or testcase setUp/tearDown (except for L34 before, which as I have argued should not have worked). But if pytest does in fact undo basicConfig between classes _somehow_, then at least this made _some_ sense.

