Got it, thanks for that. I'm nervous about taking on a new dependency just for the purpose of setting this default, but I do think it's valuable to have `lightgbm::lightgbm()` by default choose the same `num_threads` as you'd find recommended in the documentation or issues page.

And since `{RhpcBLASctl}` is on CRAN (https://cran.r-project.org/web/packages/RhpcBLASctl/index.html), we at least know it meets CRAN's rigorous standards for portability.

I'm willing to try this. To avoid imposing a new *required* dependency on users of the R package, I'm suggesting the following:

* make `num_threads = NULL` the default in `lightgbm::lightgbm()`
* add a function in https://github.com/microsoft/LightGBM/blob/master/R-package/R/utils.R like the following:
    - ```r
       .suggest_default_num_threads <- function(){
           if (require("RhcpBLASctl")) {
              return(RhcpBLASctl::get_num_cores())
          } else {
              warning("Optional package RhcpBLASctl not found. Consider
          }
          return(0L)
       }
       ```
* in `lightgbm::lightgbm()`, have code like the following
    - ```r
       if (is.null(num_threads)) {
           num_threads <- .suggest_default_num_threads()
       }
       params <- lgb.check.wrapper_param(
          main_param_name = "num_threads"
          , params = params
          , alternative_kwarg_value = num_threads
        )
       ```
* add `{RhcpBLASctl}` as a `Suggests`-level import in https://github.com/microsoft/LightGBM/blob/master/R-package/DESCRIPTION

This would avoid adding a new required dependency, and would mean that the behavior of passing `num_threads = -1` or `num_threads = 0` through keyword arg `num_threads` would have the exact same meaning, the one documented inhttps://lightgbm.readthedocs.io/en/latest/Parameters.html#num_threads and described in my comments above in this thread.

That would also encapsulate this logic so that it could optionally be re-used in the future in other parts of the package (like in setting default `num_threads` for `Dataset` construction).

