Instead of iterating through models inside RLModule let's not put any constraints on how RLModule should contain its submodules. Let's assume RLModule is the simple abstraction below:

```
class RLModule(nn.Module):
    def __init__():
          self.model1 = ...
          self.model2 = ...
    def forward_train(batch):
        # user can specify any arbitrary computational graph between submodules and then return a dict specifying everything that needs to be stored from a single forward pass for model updates
        return dict()
    def forward(batch):
        # this will be an alias to forward_train() since you mentioned DDP's assumption is that the model has a forward() interface.
        return forward_train(batch)
```

With this API you only have to ddpify the parent RLModule instead of it's children which could have implications on how its children are constructed.

